pull_request.title: GA2 - Avoid breaking change with CommunicationCallAutomationModelFactory
pull_request.body:
Renamed CommunicationCallAutomationModelFactory back to CallAutomationModelFactory with CodeGenModel.

Originally in GA1 the factory's name was CommunicationCallAutomationModelFactory. Before beta2, [autorest changed](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/pull/37518/files#diff-111ebf17c1f72cd44725d93b0f75f976931e3e7fe791d765b016898cc52584a2) it to CallAutomationModelFactory and now to avoid a breaking change (ga1 to ga2), we are renaming it back.

API diff:
https://apiview.dev/Assemblies/Review/5f7d90ecc4f341d0a6925de0f5d1f25b?diffRevisionId=a2c069a36c9941319b152ca9e3202450&diffOnly=False&revisionId=cf2ce839368e40b49e1e8ef6120c3927&doc=False

In api diff:
rev 0 is ga1
rev 1 is beta2
rev 2 is ga2 (the ARB reviewed this one, it has )
rev 3 (fixed ARB review comments)
rev 4 (current fix with CallAutomationModelFactory)
So, please compare rev3 & rev4 to see this fix, and rev4 vs rev0 to see ga1 vs latest ga2

issue.title: [BUG] DefaultAzureCredentials - Azure Identity fails (local) with v 1.10.x but works with 1.9.0

labels.name: Client
labels.description: This issue points to a problem in the data-plane of the library.

labels.name: needs-author-feedback
labels.description: More information is needed from author to address the issue.

labels.name: customer-reported
labels.description: Issues that are reported by GitHub users external to the Azure organization.

labels.name: question
labels.description: The issue doesn't require a change to the product in order to be resolved. Most issues start as that

issue.body:
### Library name and version Azure.Identity v1.10.3 ### Describe the bug This code works in Azure Identity 1.9.0 but fails in v 1.10.x fails: ``` var credentials = new DefaultAzureCredential(); var configKeys = settings["AppSettings:ConfigKeys"]?.Split('|'); config.AddAzureAppConfiguration(options => { // 1. Connect to App Configuration using the default credentials options.Connect(new Uri(settings.GetValue("AppSettings:AppConfig")), credentials); // 2. Set security for key vault as there are secrets to be resolved options.ConfigureKeyVault(kv => { kv.SetCredential(credentials); }); ``` Upgraded Azure Identity from version 1.9.0 to 1.10.0 (also tried upto recent 1.10.3), facing the below error from local environment. ![Screenshot 2023-10-26 235311](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/assets/149074998/ddd5a1b2-a952-4054-9d79-d5e46cee20e7) ### Expected behavior Authentication works without exception. ### Actual behavior When upgraded to any 1.10.x version facing the below error in local environment. ``` Azure.Identity.AuthenticationFailedException: 'ManagedIdentityCredential authentication failed: Service request failed. Status: 404 (Not Found) Content: 404 - Not Found

404 - Not Found

Headers: Date: Thu, 26 Oct 2023 18:02:55 GMT Server: EC2ws Connection: close Content-Type: text/html Content-Length: 339 See the troubleshooting guide for more information. https://aka.ms/azsdk/net/identity/managedidentitycredential/troubleshoot' ``` ### Reproduction Steps To reproduce the issue upgrade to Azure.Identity latest version ### Environment net6.0 Linux AKS Hosted on a docker-compose linux container - Works with managed identity as expected, but fails with DefaultAzureCredentials in local. Microsoft Visual Studio Professional 2022 (64-bit) Version 17.7.6 Verified local token cache in Sync from VS 2022 IDE Account Settings or Tools->Options->Azure Service Authentication

+* **Improves Search Results**: It adds secondary ranking over an initial search result set by using advanced algorithms that consider the context and meaning of the query, resulting in more relevant search outcomes.
+* **Provides Additional Information**: It also extracts and displays concise captions and answers from the search results, which can be used on a search page to improve the user's search experience.
+
+You can find detailed instructions on semantic search in the [documentation](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/search/semantic-search-overview).
